docs.abstract: Shares in the electric carmaker continued to rally after the company reported strong profits, even amid growing competition and economic pressures.
docs.snippet: Shares in the electric carmaker continued to rally after the company reported strong profits, even amid growing competition and economic pressures.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tesla investors are feeling heartened by the electric carmaker’s earnings announcement on Wednesday, which had plenty for them to like: a 59 percent year-on-year gain in quarterly profit and rising demand for its vehicles. Shares in Tesla were up nearly 7 percent in premarket trading on Thursday.

headline.main: Tesla Bulls Are Back at the Wheel
